cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.Distributed, cs.CC, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method to estimate the total time required to solve SAT in distributed environments. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper applies the proposed method to estimate the time required to perform logical cryptanalysis of stream ciphers. 
- cs.Distributed is another likely category as the paper focuses on distributed computing environments. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with hard combinatorial problems reduced to SAT. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm for searching for partitioning with an optimal solving time estimation.
